Renowned Kenyan cameraman, filmmaker and CEO of Africapix Media Sir Mohinder Dhillon launched his autobiography in a well attended event at the Oshwal Centre, Westlands on Sunday afternoon.&lsquo;My Camera, My Life&rsquo; tells of Dhillon&rsquo;s life story as one of Africa&rsquo;s foremost and best photojournalist including his experiences around the globe.Former chief justice Dr Willy Mutunga was the guest of honour at the event also attended by Caine Prize award winning author Yvonne Owour.